                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d427">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/25312: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé at Tangier (<persName type="from"
                        >Childs</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tangier</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-08T06:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 8, 1942—6 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 6:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>559. News of American landings in French North Africa was received in Tangier in
                    the early hours of the morning. Up until this hour the situation is entirely
                    normal with no more than normal circulation on the streets.</p>
                <p>Telegraph communications continue uninterruptedly, a telegram having been
                    received from the Legation in Lisbon at 4:33 a.m.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Madrid.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Childs</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
